{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}If Tag - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>If Tag</h1>

<p>The if tag conditionally renders content based on a boolean value or expression.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% if .condition %}...{% end %}
{% if .condition %}...{% else %}...{% end %}
{% if .condition %}...{% elsif .other %}...{% else %}...{% end %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Description</h2>
<p>The if tag evaluates a condition and renders content if the condition is truthy (not false, nil, or empty).</p>

<h2>Examples</h2>

<h3>Basic If - True</h3>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% if .active %}Active{% end %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Input:</strong> <code>{"active": true}</code></p>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> Active</p>

<h3>Basic If - False</h3>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% if .active %}Active{% end %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Input:</strong> <code>{"active": false}</code></p>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> (empty)</p>

<h3>If/Else</h3>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% if .status == "active" %}Active{% else %}Inactive{% end %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Input:</strong> <code>{"status": "active"}</code></p>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> Active</p>

<h3>If/Elsif/Else</h3>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% if .user.role == "admin" %}Admin{% elsif .user.role == "user" %}User{% else %}Guest{% end %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Truthy values: true, non-empty strings, non-zero numbers</li>
  <li>Falsy values: false, nil, empty string, zero</li>
  <li>Supports ==, !=, &gt;, &lt;, &gt;=, &lt;= comparisons</li>
  <li>Supports and, or, not operators</li>
</ul>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/tags/unless">unless tag</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/tags/case">case tag</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
